The final tally, a stark numerical representation of effort and fleeting glory, painted a predictable picture of regional dominance. [Brazil](/Brazil_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games) and [Cuba](/Cuba_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games), perennial powerhouses in Pan American judo, once again asserted their formidable presence. [Canada](/Canada_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games), as the host nation, managed a respectable showing, though perhaps not the overwhelming sweep some might have optimistically (or foolishly) anticipated.

