The grand total of 56 medals awarded across the 14 events meant 28 bronze medals, a generous distribution that ensured more athletes left with a tangible reminder of their effort, even if it wasn't the ultimate prize. Brazil's dominance in gold, and Cuba's consistency across all medal types, were hardly surprising. The [United States](/United_States_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games) showed a sharp focus, converting their opportunities into gold when they arose, while [Canada](/Canada_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games) demonstrated a certain knack for silver, perhaps a sign of almost-there potential.

