## Medal Table

The final medal table, a cold, hard summary of national performance, offered few surprises. Certain nations consistently demonstrate a formidable grasp of [judo](/Judo) at the Pan American level, and 2015 was no exception. [Brazil](/Brazil_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games) and [Cuba](/Cuba_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games) once again showcased their deep talent pools, while the [United States](/United_States_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games) proved capable of converting opportunities into gold. As the host nation, [Canada](/Canada_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games) secured a notable number of medals, though one might observe that a higher proportion of silver indicates a certain proximity to ultimate victory, a perpetual state of 'almost'.

Highlighted below is the host nation, [Canada](/Canada_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games), for those keeping score on home turf advantage:

