Brazil's five gold medals demonstrated a calculated precision in their training and execution, securing them the top spot despite Cuba's slightly higher overall medal count. The [United States](/United_States_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games) managed to secure three golds without a single silver, a rather efficient, if unvaried, performance. Ecuador's two golds were a stark, impactful showing, especially with no bronze medals to dilute the sharpness of their victories. Each entry in this table represents not just a nation, but countless hours of training, sacrifice, and the relentless pursuit of a brief moment of supremacy on the mat.

